author: Roger Thomas Tan
text: Nice cosy quaint place! Tuck away hidden in Hougang CC! Very few gym users in the weekday afternoon! So if it‚Äôs not too far for you - It‚Äôs A Great alternative for a gym! No one will be there to share machines with you and you really don‚Äôt have to wait! And that‚Äôs great! Machines are new with a great space between the Smith machines! The free weights area isn‚Äôt cramp and crowded- making workout great! The changing rooms are spacious, clean, well lit and nicely decorated! The toilets are outside! Belonging to the CC which means no shower areas for this gym- remember that please! Parking is easy- at the CC or the HDB behind! It‚Äôs really a nice little quiet area to work out if you want to avoid crowds on the weekday afternoon! Plus if you join this gym you get 15% off - unlike the rest of the gyms!

author: Shao Shxuan Chua
text: It's a nice cozy gym, has the general equipment and machines needed for most workouts. Comfortable to workout in.

author: Nithya
text: My PT trainer Akid is a very friendly and supportive trainer

author: Monica Isaac
text: If you prefer less crowded gym 1km radius from Kovan MRT, this is the place to be.  3 stop away from Kovan MRT Exit B bus stop via Bus 81.

author: Munny L
text:
They don't have showers :(
2 changing rooms
No row machine (for biceps)
1 squat rack
No sit-up bench
They have everything else!
Well maintained and pretty empty most of the time.

author: Yuvan Kartik
text: The customer service was great .. a new guy name Dan is actually quite humble and is very responsive when I ask questions on regards to the AF memberships.

author: Deckerz
text: Complete, clean and cozy, as a tourist this branch suit me well. Not so many people on daytime ( around 9am to 11am ).

author: SCK K
text: The gym has improved vastly after the refurbish. More space, more equipment and great staff too.

author: YJ
text:
Gym is well maintained; cleaner does a great job at cleaning as well as changing the wiping towels regularly. Best of all, the crowds aren't as large as other anytime fitness branches.

Update: the gym has removed a couple of equipments after the renovation, including the ab and hips thruster machines. Though there are new additions, they serve more like a "nice to have" than a something that compliments your workout. Additionally, the changing rooms are now smaller in size after the revamp

author: Sharon Ting

author: Hykal M
text:
Pros:
- Convenience as it is at the neighbourhood district.
- Friendly Staff
- Cleanlines is always there
- There is a toilet nearby.

Cons:
- Limited machines
- There are Gym users not putting back all the weights after they used them.
- Listening to Hardstyle/Fast Beat in the morning, in the gym, is just not my cup of coffee.

This is just my opinion and my observations each time i come to the gym in the morning. Not the best gym, nor not the worse i have been too. But overall, its still an okay gym.

author: Andrew
text:
Although small, the gym is quite clean and has all the basic workout equipment that I need. The staff manning the counter after-hours is also friendly too!

I hope that a trap-bar/decline bench press rack or a lying leg curl machine will be available in the future though.

author: ashvin nagi
text: Great staff, good selection of equipment. Gym manager, Brandon, is always there the help me whenever I need assistance. They also sell wrist wraps and other accessories for a fairly reasonable price. One of the best AF gyms in SG in my opinion

author: ÈÉ≠ÈïáË±™
text:
Very bad customer service. Constantly telling me that credit card billing failed even though the same card works fine with every other merchant and I even ensured that there's sufficient credit before payment is due. Even went down to the branch physically and the same problem reoccurred for 2 consecutive months after.

The staff will only say that this is the system and don't bother to provide any remedy or suggestions. I even had to constantly remind them of the payment issue, when they should be the ones chasing for payment instead. Also don't bother to scroll back up the chat history to check further, had to provide the exact same credit card details over Whatsapp twice and they only offer the same useless canned responses.

EDIT: They finally logged my credit card details correctly into the system but ended up double charging. Had to phone them to get photographic proof that they will not charge for the subsequent month.

author: Smiti Sagar
text: Terrible experience with their membership. Despite requesting to cancel my membership they continued to charge me for 2 more months and are still charging me and threatening to take action against me. Highly recommend to find a better gym with a more understanding management

author: Daniel Ong Ong
text: Been workout there 3 over years. It's mid size gym, located at CC which is easy to find. Always clean and tidy, no messy plates and weights around. Peak hour might be a bit crowded

author: Johnathan Loh
text:
Clean equipment, great community considering the size of the gym(it‚Äôs quite small compared to other AFs) off-peak hours is more optimal for focused training
Weekdays: 8-11am, 2-5pm, 9-11pm
Fri nights + weekends are usually quiet too which is a pro

text: The gym is clean and not too crowded most of the day. However, the treadmills are in quite poor condition lately so those intending to have a run might consider other Anytime Fitness locations.
